'''Breel Donald Embolo''' (born 14 February 1997) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Ligue 1]] club [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]] and the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]].

Born in [[Cameroon]], Embolo moved with his mother and siblings to France before finally settling in Switzerland. After working his way through their junior teams, Embolo made his professional debut for [[FC Basel|Basel]] in March 2014, and won the [[Swiss Super League]] in all three of his first seasons before moving to Germany after being signed by [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] for a reported fee of €20 million. Shortly after moving to the [[Bundesliga]], he suffered an ankle injury that ruled him out for nearly a year. He later played for [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]] before moving to Ligue 1 to play for Monaco.

Embolo made his senior international debut in 2015, earning over 80 caps. He represented Switzerland at the [[UEFA European Championship]] in [[UEFA Euro 2016|2016]], [[UEFA Euro 2020|2020]], and [[UEFA Euro 2024|2024]], and at the [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]] and [[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]].

==Early life==
Breel Donald Embolo was born on 14 February 1997, in the Cameroonian capital of [[Yaoundé]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/may/31/breel-embolo-the-rebellious-swiss-striker-with-a-charitable-cause |title=Breel Embolo: the rebellious Swiss striker with a charitable cause |website=The Guardian|date=31 May 2021 |access-date=12 June 2021}}</ref> His parents separated when he was young, and at the age of five,<ref name=":1" /> his mother moved to France where he attended school; he was raised along with his siblings between [[Toulouse]] and [[Paris]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite magazine |last=Creditor |first=Avi |title=Embolo Scores Against Birth Nation Cameroon, Doesn't Celebrate |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2022/11/24/breel-embolo-goal-switzerland-cameroon-video-world-cup |access-date=2022-11-24 |magazine=Sports Illustrated|date=24 November 2022 }}</ref> The following year, the family moved to [[Basel]], Switzerland.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/noblsp-ten-things-about-new-schalke-signing-breel-embolo.jsp |title=Ten things about new Schalke signing Breel Embolo |website=Bundesliga|access-date=12 June 2021}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Embolo started his youth football with [[FC Nordstern Basel|Nordstern]]. At the age of ten, Embolo failed his first trial with [[FC Basel|Basel]], so he moved to the [[BSC Old Boys|Old Boys]]. He was finally allowed to join the FCB youth system in their U-13 team.<ref name="AZ-2014-Embolo">{{cite web |last=Wendel |first=Sebastian |date=18 July 2014 |title=FCB shootingstar Embolo ist im Probetraining durchgefallen |url=https://www.aargauerzeitung.ch/sport/fussball/fcb-shootingstar-embolo-ist-im-probetraining-durchgefallen-ld.1850339 |access-date=27 November 2022 |publisher=Aargauer Zeitung |language=de}}</ref> In the 2011–12 and 2012–13 seasons he played in Basel's U-16. With the U-16 team he won the Swiss Championship title twice at this level.<ref name="fcb 2012-06-04">{{cite web |last=Kiesewetter |first=Dominik |year=2012 |title=U16 kurz vor der Ziellinie! |url=http://www.fcb.ch/news/show/byItemID/-/10247/28066 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140315172412/http://www.fcb.ch/news/show/byItemID/-/10247/28066 |archive-date=15 March 2014 |access-date=4 June 2012 |publisher=FC Basel 1893 |language=de}}</ref><ref name="fcb 2013-06-17">{{cite web |last=FC Basel 1893 |year=2013 |title=Die U16 holt das Double! |url=http://www.fcb.ch/news/show/byItemID/-/10247/30659 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140315184606/http://www.fcb.ch/news/show/byItemID/-/10247/30659 |archive-date=15 March 2014 |access-date=17 June 2013 |publisher=FC Basel 1893 |language=de}}</ref> He received various individual prizes, such as the Basel youngster of the year 2013.<ref name="fcb 2013-06-04">{{cite web |last=FC Basel 1893 |year=2013 |url=http://www.fcb.ch/news/show/byItemID/-/10044/30637 |title=Auszeichnung der "Rookies of the Year" |publisher=FC Basel 1893 |access-date=4 June 2013 |language=de | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140223024150/http://www.fcb.ch/news/show/byItemID/-/10044/30637 | archive-date = 23 February 2014 | url-status = dead}}</ref> On 8 March 2013, just three weeks after his 16th birthday, he signed his first professional contract with the club.<ref name="fcb 2013-03-08">{{cite web |last=FC Basel 1893 |year=2013 |title=Profivertrag für U16-Stürmer Breel-Donald Embolo |url=http://www.fcb.ch/news/show/byItemID/-/10247/29797 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140316004549/http://www.fcb.ch/news/show/byItemID/-/10247/29797 |archive-date=16 March 2014 |access-date=8 March 2013 |publisher=FC Basel 1893 |language=de}}</ref> In summer 2013 he advanced to play in their U-18 and U-21 teams.<ref name="AZ-2014-Embolo" />

===FC Basel===
During the winter break of their [[2013–14 FC Basel season|2013–14 season]], Embolo advanced to Basel's first team under head coach [[Murat Yakin]]. After appearing in two test games, Embolo made his professional debut on 13 March 2014 as a 90th-minute substitute for [[Geoffroy Serey]] in the [[2013–14 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] round of 16 first leg at [[St. Jakob-Park]].<ref name="fcb-achiv-2013/14-UEL-FCB-Salzburg">{{cite web | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 13 March 2014 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=30080 | title = FC Basel - FC Salzburg 0:0 (0:0) | format = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref> The match against [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] ended in a goalless draw.<ref name="uefa 2014-03-13">{{cite web |last=Hindley |first=Martyn |year=2014 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2012658--basel-vs-salzburg/ |title=Basel put breaks on Salzburg |publisher=[[UEFA]] |access-date=13 March 2014}}</ref> Three days later, he made his [[Swiss Super League|domestic league]] debut in the home game in the [[St. Jakob-Park]], coming on as a substitute in the 85th minute. Embolo scored his first goal for the team four minutes later, concluding a 5–0 win against [[FC Aarau|Aarau]].<ref name="fcb-achiv-2013/14-FCB-FCA">{{cite web | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 16 March 2014 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=28136 | title = FC Basel - FC Aarau 5:0 (3:0) | format = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref><ref name="AZ-2014-Embolo" /> At the end of the [[2013–14 Swiss Super League|2013–14 Super League season]] he won the league championship with Basel; they also reached the final of the [[2013–14 Swiss Cup]], but Embolo sat on the bench as they were beaten 2–0 by [[FC Zürich|Zürich]] after extra time.

In their [[2014–15 FC Basel season|2014–15 season]] new head coach was [[Paulo Sousa]], and Embolo advanced to becoming a regular player and a regular goal scorer. On 4 November 2014, he scored his first goal in the [[UEFA Champions League]], opening a 4–0 home group win against [[Ludogorets Razgrad]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Holyman |first1=Ian |title=Embolo leads Basel to Ludogorets stroll |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0253-0d0421953a0e-a839fcb75ef3-1000--embolo-leads-basel-to-ludogorets-stroll/ |access-date=5 November 2014 |publisher=UEFA |date=4 November 2014}}</ref> In the second round of the [[2014–15 Swiss Cup]], the match on 21 September in the [[Schützenwiese]], Embolo scored his first hat-trick for the team as they won 4–0 against [[FC Winterthur|Winterthur]] to advance to the next round.<ref name="fcb-achiv-2014/15-Cup-Winterthur-FCB">{{cite web | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 21 September 2014 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=30940 | title = FC Winterthur - FC Basel 0:4 (0:3) | format = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref> Basel reached the cup final, however, for the third consecutive season they finished the competition as runners-up. During the [[2014–15 Swiss Super League|2014–15 league season]], in the match at home on 12 April 2015, Embolo scored his first domestic league hat-trick as Basel won 5–1 against [[FC Zürich|Zürich]].<ref name="fcb-achiv-2014/15-FCB-FCZ">{{cite web | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | date = 12 April 2015 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/saison/spiele?command=detail&id=30230 | title = FC Basel - FC Zürich 5:1 (2:0) | format = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref> At the end of the season Basel won the championship for the sixth time in a row.<ref name="fcb-aktuell-2014/15-Championship">{{cite web |date=29 May 2015 |title=Der Meisterfreitag im bunten Zeitraffer |url=https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/2015/05/der-meisterfreitag-im-bunten-zeitraffer |access-date=27 November 2022 |publisher=FC Basel 1893 AG |language=de}}</ref> After winning the title, Embolo called [[Raphael Wicky]], the club's under-18 manager, and requested that he play their remaining games now the senior season was over.<ref name=four/>

Basel hired [[Urs Fischer (footballer)|Urs Fischer]] as their new head coach for their [[2015–16 FC Basel season|2015–16 season]]. Basel played in the [[2015–16 UEFA Europa League group stage]], and Embolo achieved two goals in eight appearances and the team completed the group stage coming top in table. Late into the 2016 January transfer window, [[VfL Wolfsburg]] made a bid for Embolo, but it was rejected by Basel. The bid was reported to be close to €27 million.<ref name="goal 2016-01-27">{{cite web |first=Joe |last=Wright |year=2016 |url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/2892/transfer-zone/2016/01/27/19725002/basel-reject-wolfsburg-bid-for-embolo |title=Basel reject Wolfsburg bid for Embolo |publisher=Goal.com |access-date=27 January 2016}}</ref> Under Fischer, Embolo won a third consecutive Swiss championship at the end of the [[2015–16 Swiss Super League|2015–16 Super League season]].<ref name="SRF-2015/16-19. Title">{{cite web | last = SRF | author-link = | date = 30 April 2016 | url = https://www.srf.ch/sport/fussball/super-league/fc-basel-holt-den-19-meistertitel | title = FC Basel holt den 19. Meistertitel | format = | work = FC Basel wins their 19th championship title | publisher = Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen (SRF) | language = de | access-date = 2022-11-16}}</ref> In June 2016, Embolo was described by ''[[FourFourTwo]]'' as "one of Europe's hottest prospects".<ref name=four>{{cite news |last1=Yokhin |first1=Michael |title=How Breel Embolo became one of Europe's hottest prospects – but won't join Man United |url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/how-breel-embolo-became-one-europes-hottest-prospects-wont-join-man-united |access-date=25 June 2016 |work=FourFourTwo |date=22 June 2016}}</ref>

On 26 June 2016 Basel announced that Embolo would leave the club and that he had signed a five-year contract. It was agreed not to disclose the terms of the transfer.<ref name="fcb-aktuell-2016-Embolo-Schalke">{{cite web |date=26 June 2016 |title=Breel Embolo wechselt zum FC Schalke 04 |url=https://www.fcb.ch/aktuell/news/1-mannschaft/2016/06/breel-embolo-wechselt-zum-fc-schalke-04 |access-date=27 November 2022 |publisher=FC Basel 1893 AG |language=de}}</ref> During his time with their first team, Embolo played a total of 91 games for Basel and scored 31 goals. 61 of these games were in the [[Swiss Super League]], six in the [[Swiss Cup]] and 24 in the UEFA competitions (Champions League and Europa League) . He scored 21 goals in the domestic league, six in the cup, and four in the European games.<ref name="fcb-achiv-Breel Donald Embolo">{{cite web | last = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | author-link = | year = 2022 | url = https://www.fcb-archiv.ch/spieler?command=detail&id=9052 | title = Breel Donald Embolo - FCB statistic | format = | publisher = Verein "Basler Fussballarchiv” | accessdate = 2022-11-16}}</ref>

===Schalke 04===
[[File:2018-08-17 1. FC Schweinfurt 05 vs. FC Schalke 04 (DFB-Pokal) by Sandro Halank–511.jpg|thumb|upright|Embolo with Schalke 04 in August 2018]]
On 26 June 2016, [[Bundesliga]] side [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] confirmed the signing of Embolo from Basel on a five-year deal, for a reported fee of €20 million plus add-ons.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://metro.co.uk/football-rumours/#5967523 |title=Done deal: Breel Embolo signs for German side Shalke |website=Metro |date=26 June 2016 |access-date=26 June 2016}}</ref> He made his debut on 20 August in the first round of the [[DFB-Pokal]] away to sixth-tier [[FC 08 Villingen]], starting and scoring in a 4–1 victory.<ref>{{cite news |title=Aogos schöner Türöffner, Embolos Abstauber|trans-title=Aogo's beautiful opener, Embolo's tap-in |url=https://www.kicker.de/villingen-gegen-schalke-2016-dfb-pokal-3309917/spielbericht |access-date=29 January 2017 |work=kicker |date=20 August 2016 |language=de}}</ref> A week later he made his league debut in a 1–0 loss at [[Eintracht Frankfurt]], replacing [[Franco Di Santo]] at half time in the season opener.<ref>{{cite news |title=Eintracht Frankfurt 1–0 FC Schalke 04 |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37206908 |access-date=29 January 2017 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 August 2016}}</ref>

He scored his first league goals for the [[Gelsenkirchen]]-based club on 2 October, a brace in a 4–0 win over [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/blmd6n-fc-schalke-04-4-0-borussia-moenchengladbach-post-match-quotes.jsp |title=Breel-iant Embolo leads Schalke plaudits after Gladbach rout |website=Bundesliga |date=12 October 2016 |access-date=17 October 2016}}</ref> Eleven days later in his next match against [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]], he suffered a serious injury following a foul from [[Kostas Stafylidis]], a complicated ankle fracture, ruptured syndesmosis and medial collateral ligament damage which ruled him out for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.espnfc.com/schalke-04/story/2974535/schalkes-breel-embolo-set-to-miss-rest-of-season-after-ankle-surgery |title=Schalke's Breel Embolo set to miss rest of season after ankle surgery |website=ESPN |last=Uersfeld |first=Stephan |date=17 October 2016 |access-date=17 October 2016}}</ref>

On 16 September 2017, Embolo made his return after missing nearly a full year of football, coming on as an 80th-minute substitute for [[Amine Harit]] in a 2–1 win at [[Werder Bremen]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Bundesliga: Breel Embolo rejoue en championnat après une année d'absence|trans-title=Bundesliga: Breel Embolo plays in the championship again after a year of absence |url=https://www.rts.ch/sport/football/8924277-bundesliga-breel-embolo-rejoue-en-championnat-apres-une-annee-dabsence.html |access-date=9 June 2018 |publisher=RTS |date=16 September 2017 |language=fr}}</ref>

===Borussia Mönchengladbach===
Embolo signed for fellow Bundesliga club Borussia Mönchengladbach on 28 June 2019 on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.borussia.de/english/team/news/borussia-news/news-detailansicht.html?tx_ttnews%5btt_news%5d=44143&cHash=6ab74a6cb42715f6e44f2289e83ab76e |title=Borussia sign Breel Embolo from Schalke 04 |publisher=Borussia Mönchengladbach |date=28 June 2019 |access-date=1 July 2019}}</ref> He made his debut in the first round of the DFB-Pokal on 9 August, coming on at half time for [[Jonas Hofmann]] in a 1–0 win at [[SV Sandhausen]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Thuram trifft beim Pflichtspieldebüt|trans-title=Thuram scores on competitive debut|url=https://rp-online.de/sport/fussball/borussia/borussia-moenchengladbach-marcus-thuram-schiesst-siegtor-in-sandhausen_aid-44983691 |access-date=13 June 2021 |date=10 August 2019 |work=Rheinische Post|language=German}}</ref> Fifteen days later, again from the bench, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3–1 win at [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz 05]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Supersub Breel Embolo inspires Borussia Mönchengladbach's come-from-behind win in Mainz |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/mainz-borussia-monchengladbach-live-line-ups-stats-ginter-mateta-embolo-6427 |access-date=13 June 2021 |publisher=Bundesliga |date=24 August 2019}}</ref>

On 27 October 2021, Embolo scored twice in a 5–0 surprise win over [[FC Bayern Munich]] in the cup second round – Bayern Munich's biggest ever defeat in the DFB-Pokal, and their first ever cup elimination to ''Gladbach''.<ref>{{cite news |title=Bayern Munich suffer historic 5-0 cup thrashing to Gladbach |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2021/10/28/football/bayern-munich-borussia-moenchengladbach-cup-spt-intl/index.html |access-date=6 November 2021 |agency=Reuters |work=CNN|date=28 October 2021}}</ref>

===Monaco===
On 15 July 2022, Embolo joined [[Ligue 1]] club [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] for a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.asmonaco.com/en/breel-embolo-is-rouge-et-blanc/ | title=Breel Embolo is 'Rouge et Blanc' | date=15 July 2022 }}</ref> The transfer fee paid to Mönchengladbach was reported as a little over €12 million.<ref>{{cite web |date=15 July 2022 |title=Für mehr als zwölf Millionen Euro: Embolo verlässt Gladbach gen Monaco |url=https://www.kicker.de/fuer-mehr-als-zwoelf-millionen-euro-embolo-verlaesst-gladbach-gen-monaco-909024/artikel |access-date=27 September 2022 |website=kicker |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Brehant |first1=Emile |date=15 July 2022 |title=L'AS Monaco tente le pari Embolo |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/football-mercato-idFRMT1IDAT0000P7X |access-date=27 September 2022 |website=Reuters |language=fr}}</ref> He made his debut on 2 August in a Champions League third qualifying round first leg at home to [[PSV Eindhoven]], as a 76th-minute substitute for [[Aleksandr Golovin (footballer)|Aleksandr Golovin]],<ref>{{cite news |date=2 August 2022 |title=Ligue des champions: les débuts d'Embolo avec Monaco |url=https://www.rts.ch/sport/football/13282821-ligue-des-champions-les-debuts-dembolo-avec-monaco.html |access-date=6 December 2022 |publisher=[[Radio Télévision Suisse]] |language=fr}}</ref> while his first league game four days later was a start in a 2–1 win at [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]].<ref>{{cite news |date=6 August 2022 |title=Ligue 1. L'AS Monaco se fait peur mais l'emporte à Strasbourg pour son premier match de la saison |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/rc-strasbourg/direct-strasbourg-monaco-suivez-la-rencontre-de-la-premiere-journee-de-ligue-1-673fb87a-14af-11ed-97a4-c5b726af28ec |access-date=6 December 2022 |work=[[Ouest-France]] |language=fr}}</ref>

On 13 August, he scored his first goal to equalize in a 1–1 draw with [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]] at the [[Stade Louis II]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Telford |first1=S. |title=Breel Embolo: 'a big season awaits Monaco' |url=https://www.ligue1.com/Articles/NEWS/2022/08/13/breel-embolo-a-big-season-awaits-monaco |access-date=6 December 2022 |publisher=Ligue 1 |date=14 August 2022}}</ref> He scored 14 goals in 40 total appearances during his first season at the club.<ref name="WF-M">{{cite web |title=Breel Embolo &raquo; Club matches |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe331158/breel-embolo/club-matches/ |website=WorldFootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |access-date=4 April 2024 |date=18 December 2021}}</ref> In the last league match of the season against [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]], Embolo came off for [[Kevin Volland]] in the closing stages of the game due to a knee injury. While undergoing individual training to regain form ahead of the [[2023–24 Ligue 1|2023–24 season]], Embolo sustained a severe [[anterior cruciate ligament injury]] during a training session, sidelining him for an extended period.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Entwistle |first1=Luke |title=Football: AS Monaco's Breel Embolo suffers severe ACL injury |url=https://monacolife.net/football-as-monacos-breel-embolo-suffers-sever-acl-injury/ |access-date=4 April 2024 |work=Monaco Life |date=7 August 2023}}</ref>

===Rennes===
On 1 September 2025, Embolo signed for fellow Ligue 1 club [[Stade Rennais FC|Rennes]] on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web | url= https://www.staderennais.com/en/news/breel-embolo-renforce-lattaque-rouge-et-noir | title= Breel Embolo, Rennes' new striker | date=1 September 2025 }}</ref> A month later, on 5 October, he netted his first goal for the club in a 2–2 away draw with [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/ligue-1/direct/direct-le-havre-rennes-suivez-le-match-de-la-7e-journee-de-ligue-1-en-live-a850cdeb-656f-472c-83b3-474be344fe8c |title=Ligue 1. Le Stade Rennais concède un nouveau match nul frustrant au Havre |publisher=Ouest-France |language=fr |date=5 October 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Breel Embolo.jpg|thumb|upright|Embolo in June 2016]]
Embolo made four appearances for the [[Switzerland national under-16 football team|Switzerland U16 national team]]. He scored his first international goal on 1 November 2012 in the 3–0 away win against the [[Ukraine national under-16 football team|Ukraine U16]]. He was also eligible to play for Cameroon, however in December 2014 he pledged his international allegiance to Switzerland.<ref>{{cite news |title=Breel Embolo chooses to play for Switzerland over Cameroon |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30484330 |access-date=1 April 2015 |work=BBC Sport |date=15 December 2014}}</ref>

He made his senior international debut on 31 March 2015, replacing [[Josip Drmić]] after 56 minutes of an eventual 1–1 friendly draw against the [[USMNT|United States]] in [[Zürich]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=McCarthy |first1=Kyle |title=Switzerland 1-1 USA: Altidore sent off in friendly draw |url=http://www.goal.com/en/match/switzerland-vs-united-states/1968679/report?ICID=MP_MS_5 |access-date=1 April 2015 |work=[[Goal (website)|Goal]] |date=31 March 2015}}</ref> On 9 October, he scored his first international goal, a penalty in a 7–0 win over [[San Marino national football team|San Marino]] at the [[AFG Arena]] in [[St Gallen]]; the result qualified the Swiss to [[UEFA Euro 2016]]. In the same game, he also set up [[Michael Lang (footballer, born 1991)|Michael Lang]] for the first goal and won a spot-kick scored by [[Johan Djourou]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Switzerland hit seven to qualify for EURO 2016 |url=https://www.uefa.com/european-qualifiers/news/0253-0d7fb27fb755-ff1f48b0baba-1000--switzerland-hit-seven-to-qualify-for-euro-2016/ |access-date=10 October 2015 |publisher=UEFA |date=9 October 2015}}</ref>

Embolo was selected by manager [[Vladimir Petković]] for the final tournament in France. A substitute in the first two group games, he then started against [[France national football team|the hosts]] in a goalless draw in [[Lille]] and came off the bench in the last 16, a 1–1 draw and [[penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]] loss to [[Poland national football team|Poland]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Johnston |first1=Neil |title=Switzerland 1–1 Poland |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36566078 |access-date=25 June 2016 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=25 June 2016}}</ref>

In [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|qualification]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], Embolo scored once to open a 2–0 win over European champions [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at his former club ground in Basel.<ref>{{cite news |title=Switzerland 2–0 Portugal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37217417 |access-date=9 June 2018 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=6 September 2016}}</ref> Petković named him for the squad to compete in the finals in Russia.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kern |first1=Max |title=Switzerland World Cup 2018 team guide: tactics, key players and expert predictions |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2018/jun/07/switzerland-world-cup-2018-team-guide-tactics-key-players-vladimir-petkovic |access-date=9 June 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=7 June 2018}}</ref>

Embolo scored once in [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]], putting the Swiss 3–0 up in an eventual 3–3 draw at home to [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] on 27 March 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Qualifs Euro 2020: la Suisse laisse échapper trois buts d'avance face au Danemark|trans-title=Euro 2020 qualifiers: Switzerland let a three-goal lead slip against Denmark|url=https://www.rts.ch/sport/football/international/equipe-suisse/10320058-qualifs-euro-2020-la-suisse-laisse-echapper-trois-buts-davance-face-au-danemark.html |access-date=13 June 2021 |publisher=RTS |date=27 March 2019 |language=French}}</ref> At the [[UEFA Euro 2020|major tournament]], held in 2021, he scored the opener in their first group game, a 1–1 draw with [[Wales national football team|Wales]] in [[Baku]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Young |first1=Alex |title=Wales 1–1 Switzerland: Kieffer Moore cancels out Breel Embolo header to earn Euros draw |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/wales-vs-switzerland-euro-2021-result-score-embolo-moore-goal-b940255.html |access-date=13 June 2021 |work=Evening Standard |date=12 June 2021}}</ref>

In Switzerland's first game of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] against Cameroon, Embolo scored the only goal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=World Cup 2022 final score: Switzerland downs Cameroon as Breel Embolo's goal makes history in 1–0 win |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/world-cup-2022-final-score-switzerland-downs-cameroon-as-breel-embolos-goal-makes-history-in-1-0-win/live/ |access-date=2022-11-24 |website=CBS Sports|date=24 November 2022 }}</ref> He was the second player in World Cup history to score against the country of his birth; the first was [[Alfred Bickel]], also for Switzerland, against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] in [[1938 FIFA World Cup|1938]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hamilton |first1=Tom |title=Breel Embolo haunts Cameroon as Switzerland claim crucial World Cup win |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/37634041/embolo-haunts-cameroon-switzerland-claim-crucial-win |access-date=27 May 2024 |publisher=ESPN |date=24 November 2022}}</ref> Out of respect, Embolo chose not to celebrate, standing still with his hands up to his face as his teammates mobbed him and did the more vigorous celebrating.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-11-24 |title=Switzerland 1–0 Cameroon: Breel Embolo nets winner in tight Group G opener |url=https://www.football365.com/news/switzerland-1-0-cameroon-breel-embolo-nets-winner-in-tight-group-g-opener |access-date=2022-11-24 |website=Football365}}</ref> In the final group game against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]], he equalized as the Swiss came from behind to win 3–2 and advance to the last 16.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Robson |first1=James |title=Switzerland beats Serbia 3–2 to reach last 16 of World Cup |url=https://apnews.com/article/switzerland-serbia-2022-world-cup-results-53634c193b935199360015e80d44ef00 |access-date=27 May 2024 |publisher=Associated Press |date=2 December 2022}}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=Männer-Nationalteam: Das EM-Kader steht – Zeqiri reist nicht nach Deutschland |trans-title=Men’s national team: The European Championship squad is set – Zeqiri will not travel to Germany |url=https://www.football.ch/sfv/nationalteams/a-team/news/maenner-nationalteam-das-em-kader-steht-zeqiri-reist-nicht-nach-deutschland.aspx |language=de |publisher=[[Swiss Football Association]] |access-date=7 June 2024}}</ref> On 15 June, he scored a stoppage-time goal, securing a 3–1 victory over [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]] in Switzerland's opening match of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://apnews.com/article/hungary-switzerland-euro-2024-168f7a1e4eb75bce53a3a74cdc7eb15e |title=Switzerland holds on to beat Hungary 3-1 at Euro 2024 |publisher=AP News |date=15 June 2024 }}</ref>

On 20 May 2026, he was named in Switzerland's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.football.ch/sfv/nationalteams/a-team/news/maenner-nationalteam-murat-yakins-aufgebot-mit-18-wm-erfahrenen-spielern.aspx |title=Männer-Nationalteam: Murat Yakins Aufgebot mit 18 WM-erfahrenen Spielern |trans-title=Men's National Team: Murat Yakin's roster features 18 players with World Cup experience |publisher=[[Swiss Football Association]] |date=May 20, 2026 |access-date=May 20, 2026 |language=de |archive-date=May 21, 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260521100452/https://www.football.ch/sfv/nationalteams/a-team/news/maenner-nationalteam-murat-yakins-aufgebot-mit-18-wm-erfahrenen-spielern.aspx |url-status=live}}</ref> His participation was initially in doubt after he was denied entry to the United States due to a 2023 conviction for making threats, for which he received a suspended fine.<ref>{{cite web |last=Brotherton |first=Alex |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/ckgpkw8zzx1o |title=Switzerland travel to US without Embolo over Esta issue |publisher=BBC Sport |date=2 June 2026 }}</ref> He was later granted entry clearance and remained eligible to participate in the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sanghera |first=Mandeep |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cn8p894wyq8o |title=Switzerland's Embolo granted approval to travel to US |publisher=BBC Sport |date=4 June 2026 }}</ref>

==Style of play==
[[File:Loco-Shal04 (3).jpg|thumb|Embolo challenging with [[Benedikt Höwedes]] of [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow|Lokomotiv Moscow]] in October 2018]]
[[UEFA|UEFA.com]] writer Steffen Potter praised Embolo as a complete striker: "He is powerful, technically strong and decisive. He has explosive pace and is a composed finisher." [[Fabian Frei]], who was a [[midfielder]] for [[FC Basel]] at the same time with Embolo, complimented him as well, for keeping his feet on the ground.<ref name="WK">{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0253-0d042a005d82-4665581dbe62-1000--uefa-com-s-weekly-wonderkid-breel-embolo/ |title=UEFA.com's weekly wonderkid: Breel Embolo |publisher=[[UEFA]] |date=7 February 2015}}</ref><blockquote>I think he is a sensation – playing like that aged 17. I like him as a person as much as I do as a player. His feet will stay on the ground – he won't be shooting from 50 metres to score the goal of the season. You can give him good advice and he is ready to take it without getting angry.</blockquote>

Embolo has cited [[Mario Balotelli]] as one of his inspirations. Both players like to lurk between defenders, and both have great control allied to physical prowess.<ref name="WK" />

Embolo can also play in [[midfield]]; according to David Lemos of [[Radio Télévision Suisse]] he resembles [[N'Golo Kanté]] in this role, using his power to retrieve the ball and give it to the attackers.<ref name="four" />

== Personal life ==
At the age of 18, he created the Embolo Foundation to support refugee children in Switzerland and disadvantaged youth in his birth country of Cameroon.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news |last=Bradshaw |first=Joe |date=November 24, 2022 |title=Embolo gives Swiss opening win over Cameroon |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63657470 |access-date=2022-11-24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Sugimoto |first=Takashi |date=2022-05-21 |title=Sport has the power to unite |url=https://thephilanthropist.ch/en/sport-has-the-power-to-unite/ |access-date=2022-11-24 |website=THE PHILANTHROPIST |language=de-DE}}</ref> Embolo received [[Swiss nationality law|Swiss citizenship]] in 2014.<ref name="blick 2014-12-12">{{cite web |last=Kreis |first=Stefan |author2=Sandro Inguscio |year=2014 |title=FCB-Star Embolo erhält den Schweizer Pass! |url=http://www.blick.ch/sport/fussball/nati/buhlen-von-etoo-umsonst-fcb-star-embolo-erhaelt-den-schweizer-pass-id3342858.html |access-date=12 December 2014 |publisher=blick.ch |language=de}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=12 December 2014 |title=FCB-Stürmer Breel Embolo erhält den Schweizer Pass |url=http://www.srf.ch/news/regional/basel-baselland/fcb-stuermer-breel-embolo-erhaelt-den-schweizer-pass |access-date=12 December 2014 |publisher=[[Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen]] |language=de}}</ref> He had to renounce his Cameroonian citizenship because Cameroon does not recognize dual citizenship.<ref>[https://www.srf.ch/sport/fussball/nationalmannschaft/nationalmannschaft-embolo-entscheidet-sich-fuer-die-schweiz ''Embolo entscheidet sich für die Schweiz.''] In: ''SRF.ch'', 15. Dezember 2014.</ref> 
Embolo has two children with his girlfriend Naomi; his daughter was born in 2018 and his son in 2019.<ref>[https://www.blick.ch/sport/fussball/em/nati-stuermer-im-portrait-das-muessen-sie-ueber-breel-embolo-wissen-id16561679.html ''Das müssen Sie über Breel Embolo wissen.''] In: ''Blick.ch'', 1. Juni 2021.</ref>

